And now she slowely rode towards the neutral grounds that seperated the known amazon lands from the outsiders.  Dressed in her old war leathers, she wore the mask of war over her head and face.  She looked more like a wild bird woman upon that large grey mare then anything else.  Her armour was heavily decorated with emblems of Hera and wild horses stampeding.  Across her waist, she wore the belt given to her by her father, Ares.  Unlike many of the amazons who were making their marks now adays.  Hippolyte was one of the southern amazons.  Tribes that were brought up under the beliefs of the Olympian Gods.  Daughters of Ares these women were called.  And some of them, like Hippolyte, were the war gods children by actual birth.  Under her mask, her face was stern.  The edge of the amazon lands was being threatened.  And she would not allow it.<br>
As she rode along, she chanted in an almost hiss to her goddess, Hera.  Her brown eyes were set and hard as she gazed thru her mask.  Her small but strong hands held the reigns in one hand and in the other a long slim scimitar that rested next to one of her thighs.   Her heart beating in the rythem of the chant, Hippolyte was ready and firm in her convictions. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>
