&quot;To a strong amazon nation!&quot;, she cried.  Quickly, the amazon rode her chestnut horse up near the others, but not next to them.  An amazon who rarely met up with her sister amazons.  Penthesilea had long allied herself with the Trojans.  But word had gotten out that a war was declared.  And Penth was not one to ignore it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 392<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/13/01 7:35:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~War~</span><hr size=1>  A war without the Queen of the Assassins, was well, not smart to say the least. For the last couple of months, the immortal amazon assassin had been playing things safe, staying out of the cross fire, and staying out of the fights. But one thing be known, you can't keep a good woman [or man] down, and welp, that blood lust was going to proove it in this war. <br>
